snippet.textDisplay:
Damn. Thames reminds me so much of the Hudson between Jersey and NYC. I used to go on lonely drunken strolls there and listen to Krule, and I remember even climbing onto a huge hunk of metal in the water drunkenly singing his songs. Carried his music with me for years and it all hit so deep. The Locomotive takes me back to when I was drunkenly screaming in the night on train tracks. Dum Surfer takes me back to when I was puking on pavement slabs. Out Getting Ribs hits me where I carry my father's anger and lost so much faith in love and trust.

Now I'm 20 days sober and going to AA meetings (for agnostics/atheists) and I feel loads better. Knowing that Archy is also climbing out of his depression means a lot to me. I'm gonna see him for the first time and you bet I'm gonna be wailing my heart out.

snippet.textDisplay: Everybody in the comments is speaking about how this is such a good, and positive song. But I just broke up with my girlfriend of 3 years, and don’t really think I ended it right. I told her not to contact me anymore. This song is just hurting me, taking me through the motions. My ex has her dilemmas and issues that I know of and see her go through. I really want to help, but that’s no longer my position. I just want her to be okay and I want her to know that she’s not alone, she will always have a place for in my heart, I constantly worry about her even though I know she doesn’t feel the same.
